OL,3,CWhat are my rights if my flight is
OL,4,Cdelayed or cancelled?
OL,6,FAccording to the Civil Aviation
OL,7,FAuthority (CAA), an airline must
OL,8,Fprovide a reasonable amount of food
OL,9,Fand drink in the case of a
OL,10,F"significant delay".
OL,12,FWhat is classed as a significant delay?
OL,14,FThis usually comes in the form of
OL,15,Fvouchers, but if an airline cannot
OL,16,Fprovide food and drink or voucher
OL,17,Fequivalent for whatever reason,
OL,18,Fcustomers can make their own
OL,19,F"reasonable" arrangements and keep
OL,20,Ftheir receipts to claim the money back.
